steps.name: Set Maven in Global Tools Configuration with Maven name 'qbQN7cfBe1L8BKx'
Switch to the side menu
Click on 'Manage Jenkins' link on the side menu
Click 'Global Tool Configuration' link in 'System Configuration' section
Set Maven version in Global Tools Configuration with new Maven name '{name}'
Switch to Breadcrumbs panel
Click on 'Dashboard' link
Create Freestyle project with valid random name and return to dashboard
Switch to the side menu
Click 'New Item' on the Side Menu
Input the New Item name: 0M98sBZTZNbfKrp
Select 'Freestyle project' type on NewItemPage
Click 'OK' button
Click 'Save' button on the configuration page
Switch to header
Click on 'Jenkins' name icon on the header
Select ‘Freestyle project’ '0M98sBZTZNbfKrp' on the Dashboard
Switch to the side menu
Click 'Configure' on side menu
Select 'Git' radio button in the 'Source Code Management' section of the Configuration page
Input 'https://github.com/RedRoverSchool/JenkinsQA_05-test.git' in the 'Repository URL' field. Refer to TestDataUtils.GITHUB_REPOSITORY_URL
Input '*/main' in the 'Branch Specifier' field
Open ‘Add Build Steps' dropdown in the ‘Build Steps' section
Select ‘Invoke top-level Maven targets’ in dropdown menu of the 'Build Steps' section
Select Maven version with name 'qbQN7cfBe1L8BKx' in dropdown of the 'Maven version' field in the 'Invoke top-level Maven targets' section
Set ‘test’ in ‘Goals’ field
Click 'Save' button on the configuration page
Switch to the side menu
Click 'Build Now' on the side menu and wait for all builds are completed with 'Success' result'
